WorldStage Newsonline– Africa Prudential Plc, a leading share registration firm, investor and business support services provider in Nigeria said its Board of Directors has  recommended payment of dividend of 50 Kobo per ordinary share, amounting to N1 billion for approval of shareholders at the Annual General Meeting The company in a notification at the Nigerian Stock Exchange on Friday said the recommendation was made at the meeting of the Board held on Thursday February 18, 2021during when the company’s audited financial statements for the year ended December 31, 2020 was approved.